     <section class="title"> 
      <section class="wrapper"> 
       <h1>Chinese Studies</h1> 
      </section> 
     </section> 
     <section class="whatisthis"> 
      <header>
       What if you could...
      </header> 
      <section>
       <p>What if you could learn modern standard Chinese, or 普通話, from Professor Bai Di, a native of Harbin, China...</p> 
      </section> 
     </section> 
    </header> 
    <section id="about" class="about"> 
     <h2><strong>Chinese Studies</strong> explores one<br> of the world’s most powerful<br> shapers of the future</h2> 
    </section> 
    <section id="thefacts" class="thefacts">
     <div id="carousel-thefacts" class="touchcarousel drew resize ">
      <ul class="touchcarousel-container"> 
       <li class="touchcarousel-item ">
        <section> 
         <h2>PASSPORT TO A FIFTH OF HUMANITY</h2> 
         <p>There are over a billion Chinese speakers,<br> which translates to about one out of every five humans.<br> <strong>Chinese speakers outnumber English speakers by about 2 to 1</strong>.<br> </p>
        </section></li> 
       <li class="touchcarousel-item ">
        <section>
          Our major gives you 
         <strong>much more than just language</strong>. Students learn in depth about China’s history, literature, politics and contemporary society.
         <br> 
        </section></li> 
       <li class="touchcarousel-item ">
        <section> 
         <strong>Issues of culture in China are headline news</strong> as it struggles with rapid change. A group of Drew students and faculty recently used a $25,000 research grant to travel to China and study women’s education.
         <br> 
        </section></li> 
       <li class="touchcarousel-item ">
        <section>
          As the world’s fastest-growing economy, the speed of change in China is breathtaking and momentous. With the skills you learn as a Drew Chinese Studies major you can 
         <strong>be a part of this history</strong>.
         <br> 
        </section></li> 
      </ul>
     </div> 
    </section> 
